Watchlist

Where to Watch

Best Actress nominee Judi Dench and Bob Hoskins bring down the house as a plucky matron of the arts and a polished impresario who get involved in some risque business during World War II when they open a London theater that offers nude entertainment. The rollicking fact-based film is directed by Stephen Frears, and Hopkins serves as executive producer. British pop star Will Young costars as Bertie. Kelly Reilly, Christopher Guest, Thelma Barlow.
